details:
Case 174 is a 67 year-old female Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. She is warded in an isolation room at National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID). She is a contact of Case 122 and is linked to the cluster involving the private dinner function at SAFRA Jurong.Â 

As she had been identified as a contact of Case 122, she was placed under quarantine on 6 March. She reported onset of symptoms on 7 March, and subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 11 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, she had mostly stayed at her home at Gangsa Road.
